{
  "texts": [
    "First, because it clouds our eyes to the ambiguity of diversity as an instrumental and thus conditional value.",
    "Second, because such portrayals often lead to a treatment of diversity as a resource that can be \"exploited.\"",
    "Political philosopher Iris Young, however, warned already in the 1980 s against such capitalist appropriations of the concept, where diversity is instrumentalized as something that \"enriches me\" or as a means of optimally valorizing people.",
    "Instead, diversity is about how we can live together in an inclusive, participatory, and nondiscriminatory way (Young, 1990).",
    "To clarify this difference, anthropologist Anna Tsing speaks of \"meaningful diversity,\" that is, diversity that changes things, as opposed to scalable diversity, which accepts only what can be incorporated into pre-existing standards without further adaptation (Tsing, 2012)."
  ]
}